
Overview of noun remedy

The noun remedy has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (2) redress, remedy, remediation -- (act of correcting an error or a fault or an evil)
2. (1) remedy, curative, cure, therapeutic -- (a medicine or therapy that cures disease or relieve pain)

Overview of verb remedy

The verb remedy has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) rectify, remediate, remedy, repair, amend -- (set straight or right; "remedy these deficiencies"; "rectify the inequities in salaries"; "repair an oversight")
